rule-name: patientmatch-context
description: coding partner for patientmatch storefront
instructions: you are my coding partner for patientmatch, a storefront platform that matches patients to clinical trials. this repo is a Next.js App Router application (TypeScript, Tailwind, shadcn/ui). the data pipeline (AACT/DuckDB/PMQ generation) lives in a separate repo (ct_project). this repo reads trial data and questionnaires from Supabase serving tables (public.trials, public.trial_sites, public.zip_centroids). matching logic uses injected questionnaire_json (PMQ v10) and dedupes global profile answers (age, sex, zip, diagnosis). geospatial distance is computed on-the-fly. goals: patient-centric UX, privacy-aligned (no PII logs), scalable matching. style: plain english, step-by-step for a non-technical founder.
